 proprietary intellectual property leaks.\"\n 41 |   },\n 42 |   {\n 43 |     id: \"human-loop\",\n 44 |     title: \"3. Human-in-the-Loop Gate\",\n 45 |     subtitle: \"Manual Oversight\",\n 46 |     desc: \"Actions exceeding predefined risk bounds are frozen, routing to authorized administrators for manual review.\"\n 47 |   },\n 48 |   {\n 49 |     id: \"execution\",\n 50 |     title: \"4. Sandbox Execution\",\n 51 |     subtitle: \"Hermetic Sandbox\",\n 52 |     desc: \"The agent executes inside an isolated container with read-only system memory and restricted database connection pools.\"\n 53 |   },\n 54 |   {\n 55 |     id: \"ledger\",\n 56 |     title: \"5. Immutable Log\",\n 57 |     subtitle: \"Cryptographic Audit\",\n 58 |     desc: \"All queries, state changes, and human approvals are written to an immutable, cryptographically-signed execution ledger.\"\n 59 |   }\n 60 | ];\n 61 | \n 62 | export default function RuntimeGovernancePage() {\n 63 |   const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState<\"firewalls\" | \"oversight\" | \"ledger\">(\"firewalls\");\n 64 |   const [activeStep, setActiveStep] = useState(\"guardrails\");\n 65 |   const [policies, setPolicies] = useState({\n 66 |     pii: true,\n 67 |     injection: true,\n 68 |     boundary: true,\n 69 |     toxicity: false\n 70 |   });\n 71 |   \n 72 |   // Human approval simulation states\n 73 |   const [pendingActions, setPendingActions] = useState([\n 74 |     {\n 75 |       id: \"ACT-841\",\n 76 |       agent: \"Operations Broker\",\n 77 |       action: \"Initiate SAP freight update for $48,200 invoice variance\",\n 78 |       status: \"pending\",\n 79 |       severity: \"high\"\n 80 |     },\n 81 |     {\n 82 |       id: \"ACT-842\",\n 83 |       agent: \"Knowledge Synthesizer\",\n 84 |       action: \"Export client contract summary to S3 bucket\",\n 85 |       status: \"pending\",\n 86 |       severity: \"medium\"\n 87 |     }\n 88 |   ]);\n 89 | \n 90 |   const handleAction = (id: string, approve: boolean) => {\n 91 |     setPendingActions(prev => \n 92 |       prev.map(act => act.id === id ? { ...act, status: approve ? \"approved\" : \"rejected\" } : act)\n 93 |     );\n 94 |   };\n 95 | \n 96 |   const currentStepData = GOVERNANCE_STEPS.find(s => s.id === activeStep) || GOVERNANCE_STEPS[1];\n 97 | \n 98 |   return (\n 99 |     <InnerPageShell>\n100 |       <InnerPageHero\n101 |         category=\"Platforms & Modules\"\n102 |         title=\"Continuous Runtime Governance and Risk Firewalls\"\n103 |         highlightedWord=\"Governance\"\n104 |         highlightColor=\"gradient\"\n105 |         description=\"Enforce strict operational boundaries, deterministic human-in-the-loop oversight, and immutable cryptographic ledgers over multi-agent workflows.\"\n106 |         breadcrumbs={[{ label: \"Platforms\", href: \"/platforms\" }, { label: \"Runtime Governance\" }]}\n107 |       />\n108 | \n109 |       <div className=\"max-w-[1795px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16 pb-24 space-y-24\">\n110 |         \n111 |         {/* Board Alignment Editorial Banner */}\n112 |         <MotionReveal className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 py-12 border-y border-white/5 items-center bg-white/[0.01] px-8 rounded-2xl relative overflow-hidden\">\n113 |           <div className=\"absolute top-0 right-0 w-[30%] h-full bg-gradient-to-l from-[#E4000F]/5 to-transparent pointer-events-none\" />\n114 |           <div className=\"lg:col-span-5\">\n115 |             <span className=\"text-xs font-mono text-red-500 uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">The Boardroom Challenge</span>\n116 |             <h2 className=\"text-3xl font-semibold text-white tracking-tight mt-2\">Guarding Enterprise Integrity</h2>\n117 |           </div>\n118 |           <div className=\"lg:col-span-7\">\n119 |             <p className=\"text-white/70 font-light text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed\">\n120 |               True corporate automation requires rigorous risk mitigation. Rather than hoping that foundational models remain safe, GFF enforces a <strong className=\"text-white font-medium\">governance-first paradigm</strong>. By isolating cognitive modeling inside secure containers and intercepting prompts and tools at the network level, we isolate threats, preserve system integrity, and provide auditability—without guaranteeing compliance or offering fake legal checklists.\n121 |             </p>\n122 |           </div>\n123 |         </MotionReveal>\n124 | \n125 |         {/* Section 1: Interactive Governance Shield Diagram */}\n126 |         <MotionReveal className=\"space-y-10\">\n127 |           <div className=\"text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto space-y-2\">\n128 |             <span className=\"text-xs font-mono text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">The Gatekeeper Stack</span>\n129 |             <h2 className=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight\">Active Sequence Flow</h2>\n130 |             <p className=\"text-white/50 text-sm font-light\">Trace the life of an execution payload from ingress interception to cryptographic archival.</p>\n131 |           </div>\n132 | \n133 |           <div className=\"bg-[#050505]/60 border border-white/5 p-6 lg:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl relative overflow-hidden\">\n134 |             <div className=\"absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[60%] h-[1px] bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[#E4000F]/30 to-transparent\" />\n135 |             \n136 |             {/* Horizontal Timeline Graph for Desktop, Stacking on Mobile */}\n137 |             <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-5 gap-4 relative z-10 pb-8 border-b border-white/5\">\n138 |               {GOVERNANCE_STEPS.map((step) => {\n139 |                 const isActive = step.id === activeStep;\n140 |                 return (\n141 |                   <div\n142 |                     key={step.id}\n143 |                     onClick={() => setActiveStep(step.id)}\n144 |                     className={`p-4 rounded-xl border transition-all cursor-pointer text-center group ${\n145 |                       isActive \n146 |                         ? \"border-[#E4000F] bg-[#E4000F]/5\" \n147 |                         : \"border-white/5 bg-black hover:border-white/10\"\n148 |                     }`}\n149 |                   >\n150 |                     <div className={`w-8 h-8 rounded-full mx-auto flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold font-mono transition-colors ${\n151 |                       isActive ? \"bg-[#E4000F] text-white\" : \"bg-white/5 text-white/50 group-hover:text-white\"\n152 |                     }`}>\n153 |                       {step.id === \"ingress\" && \"1\"}\n154 |                       {step.id === \"guardrails\" && \"2\"}\n155 |                       {step.id === \"human-loop\" && \"3\"}\n156 |                       {step.id === \"execution\" && \"4\"}\n157 |                       {step.id === \"ledger\" && \"5\"}\n158 |                     </div>\n159 |                     <h3 className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white mt-3 uppercase tracking-wider\">{step.subtitle}</h3>\n160 |                     <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/30 block mt-1\">{step.title}</span>\n161 |                   </div>\n162 |                 );\n163 |               })}\n164 |             </div>\n165 | \n166 |             {/* Selected Step Inspector Panel */}\n167 |             <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-center pt-8 relative z-10 min-h-[160px]\">\n168 |               <div className=\"lg:col-span-8 space-y-3\">\n169 |                 <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n170 |                   <span className=\"px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-[9px] bg-[#E4000F]/15 text-[#E4000F] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border border-[#E4000F]/20\">\n171 |                     Active Step Inspector\n172 |                   </span>\n173 |                   <span className=\"text-xs font-mono text-white/40\">{\"// SYSTEM_FLOW_\"}{activeStep.to